Description . Male . Measurements: BL 7.60, CL 4.35, CW 3.30, PLE 0.35, PME 0.30 (QM 1373). Female . Measurements: BL 11.70, CL 4.75, CW 3.75, PLE 0.40, PME 0.35 (QM S1372). For morphological description see species diagnosis and generic description.

Distribution . Known from south east Queensland to south east Victoria ( Fig. 27d ). This is the most widely distributed species of
Storenosoma
.
Remarks . The female holotype has the epigynum plugged.
